{
  "stem": "20083.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, the fact is that I did not join either the Hitler Youth or the Jungvolk.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's the organization before you join the Hitler Youth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most of them actually had joined, but they were still quite a few Christian or Aryan boys who did not join.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I don't know if they ever did join, but, so I was not sticking out like a sore thumb in a big crowd.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I never felt any backlash as far as my religion was concerned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, to my knowledge, there were none, at least in my class.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know about the rest of the school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the-- before Hitler came to power in 1933, I felt absolutely no anti-semitism.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was simply, as far as I was concerned as a child, was not aware of it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And just never saw any overt signs of anti-semitism.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Afterwards, I must say that, in my school, I did not experience any-- any anti-semitism either, except for one incident of a man who lived above us who was a member of the SS.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he had fallen in love with my sister, who was 10 years older than I am, Anne Marie.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he tried to court her, even though he was married himself.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when one day he visited us, I had to tell him, around 1935 or 1936-- I can't remember the exact year-- that we were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he got such a shock that he slapped me and called me a [GERMAN] and simply said that he didn't want to have anything to do with us anymore and left.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was the last we saw of him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In-- in no way.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Non-- we were not affiliated with anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As far as religion was concerned, it was not mentioned.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
